{
  "$schema": "./scheduled-jobs.schema.json",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "status": "design",
  "bead": "BB-084",
  "environment": "blackbook-internal",
  "policyPackageRef": "packages/config/src/scheduled-jobs/roster.ts",
  "notes": [
    "Declarative mirror only — not applied to live GCP. Apply via Terraform or `gcloud scheduler jobs create` after human review, per ADR-007 (Cloud Scheduler -> Cloud Tasks -> Cloud Run Jobs).",
    "packages/config/src/scheduled-jobs/roster.ts is authoritative; this file is the Cloud-Scheduler-facing declarative projection of the same registry and must be kept in sync by hand, same convention as infra/gcp/cost-controls/cost-controls-matrix.json mirroring packages/security/src/resource-controls.ts.",
    "rosterStatus 'stub' entries have a registered schedule and target, but the target function does not exist yet — a Cloud Scheduler job pointing at one would no-op/fail-closed until the owning bead ships the handler. That is intentional: the schedule is declared now so its cadence/budget/kill-switch shape is reviewed once, not invented ad hoc later.",
    "publicEffect 'link-repair-archived-copy' and 'release-coupled-rebuild' are the only two jobs allowed any automatic public-facing effect at all (BB-084 invariant); every other job's output is a private candidate/report/flag for human review.",
    "environment is the BB-078/ADR-012 project name (blackbook-internal), not a numeric GCP project id — BB-079 has not run a live apply yet."
  ],
